Update only the **header HTML + CSS** like this.

## `sales-points.html`

Replace your header with:

```html
<header class="page-header">
    <img class="logo" th:src="@{/images/cetelem-logo.svg}" alt="Cetelem">

    <div class="language-selector" aria-label="Language selector">
        <button type="button" class="language-btn active">FR</button>
        <button type="button" class="language-btn">NL</button>
    </div>
</header>
```

## `sales-points.css`

Replace/add header CSS:

```css
.page-header {
    height: 96px;
    padding: 16px 112px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #ffffff;
    background: #ffffff;
}

.logo {
    width: 140px;
    height: auto;
}

.language-selector {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 4px;
}

.language-btn {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: transparent;
    color: #154734;
    font-family: "Open Sans", Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.language-btn.active {
    background: #154734;
    color: #ffffff;
}
```

## Mobile CSS

Add inside your mobile media query:

```css
@media (max-width: 520px) {
    .page-header {
        height: 72px;
        padding: 16px 24px;
    }

    .logo {
        width: 120px;
    }

    .language-btn {
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        font-size: 16px;
    }
}
```

This matches the Figma header: logo left, FR/NL right, active FR round dark green button.
